column5: Nice report!  Made me wish I had gotten to know the Larry a little better while I was in Montreal, its an awesome fishery.  Congrats on the 50.
Great report and pics irishfield  That is a big and beautiful ski for sure    Congrats  Thanks for sharing Leechman
Nice report and pics! That is a huge musky, must be a PB eh?
Great Report Irishfield!  Looks like it was a blast!  Congrats on that MASSIVE musky!

You guys boated some nice fish, but there was a whole lot more to the trip than just catching.  Thanks for bring us the report.  One problem though.  I don't think you should have cooked and eaten Dan's hand.  What's wrong with you Canadians?
Yes there was Connie.... we're just not allowed to talk about it yet!
Love this report and what a great catch but ... did somebody forget to feed Roy? The ski has a wider mid section!
Super report Wayne and a job well done by Marc eventhough conditions have been tough this year.  good thing you went to Roy's for dinner the hand looked good until ya burnt it
Excellent Wayne, congrat's on the bigun' and a fantastic report!
Great report and pics....thanks guys.  I'm just glad to see Thorpe is still able to walk.
Great thick clean looking fish! Congrats that is awesome!
HH
great report wayne thats one big ski awesome
Awesome Musky !!!!!  Looks like a great time... thanks for the report!
Fabulous, Wayne, Dano.  Great muskies from the Larry.  Topping it off with some of Roy and Jeanne's hospitality made that a perfect trip.
Glad you enjoyed your trip guys. Very nice seeing you folks again. Thanks for the kind words.
Nice catches guys, now you need to go and find your own monsters without depending on a guide.
Great report Wayne.  Those were some great looking 'skis.  Not so great weather but the company I'm sure made up for it all.  Thanks for sharing.  Stan

On account of last years bum-whipping you two yahoos put on the Larryskis I would say this years results were a little bit of a fishes revenge.  But, that's fishing... muskie fishing at that.  Dan got the biggest last year didn't he???  Guess you fellas are even now.  Great fish Wayne, GREAT!  Enjoyed the installment doods.  Ti'll next year I guess.

Hey Wayne and  Dan aka (R...... R.......) Take it like a man  Tks for the wonderful time,once again great laughs and time Beyond the fish we were in stitches most of the time,Dan and Wayne are funny Tks to Roy and J for the great feed,as usual its scrumptious This year has been good,with numbers down somewhat but overall great big ones the same as years previous High water has spread fish out and basically taken their 10 year cycle of home ranges away from them ,so many fish are roaming searching themselves somewhat because of areas previously being low water areas and this year opening many new areas in which the fish can use  I see Wayne you have not had your hair cut yet I think you would look good like this
Great report guys....
Beautiful Muskie Wayne!  Congrats on the tanker!

Super report guys     And Supper with J and Roy, sounds like the perfect trip  That is a beautiful fish Wayne, I also like the underbite.  Love the bbq'd hand bit, that's hilarious.  Fern is right  Joey
Supertanker for sure. Great job guys. Always a blast fishin with the magician. Looks to be about 48.........
Great report.... man that Thorpe dude, sure isnt aging well...lol   - oh wait.. that was ROY!!  :whistling:
